.\" pdftofilteredtext(1) man page
.TH pdftofilteredtext 1 "February 2026" "poppler" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
pdftofilteredtext \- PDF to plain text converter with automatic invalid-unicode filtering
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pdftofilteredtext
[\fIoptions\fR] \fIPDF-file\fR [\fItext-file\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pdftofilteredtext
converts PDF documents to plain text, automatically removing characters
that cannot be mapped to valid Unicode code points.  Characters in the
following ranges are silently discarded:
.TP
U+0000
Null character
.TP
U+0001\(enU+001F
ASCII control characters
.TP
U+D800\(enU+DFFF
Lone surrogate code points
.TP
U+E000\(enU+F8FF
Private Use Area (PUA)
.TP
U+FFFD
Unicode Replacement Character (marks a decoding failure)
.PP
This behaviour is especially useful for PDFs that embed Type3 or CID fonts
with incomplete or absent ToUnicode CMaps, which often produce large numbers
of unmappable glyphs that clutter the extracted text.
.PP
If \fItext-file\fR is not given, the output is written to
\fIPDF-file\fR\fB.txt\fR (replacing or stripping a \fB.pdf\fR extension).
Specify \fB\-\fR as \fItext-file\fR to write to standard output.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-f " number"
First page to convert.  Default: 1.
.TP
.BI \-l " number"
Last page to convert.  Default: last page of the document.
.TP
.B \-layout
Maintain the original physical layout of the text on the page.
.TP
.BI \-fixed " pitch"
Assume fixed-pitch (tabular) text with the given character cell width
(in points).
.TP
.B \-raw
Keep strings in content-stream order instead of re-ordering them
for reading.
.TP
.BI \-opw " password"
Owner password for encrypted PDF files.
.TP
.BI \-upw " password"
User password for encrypted PDF files.
.TP
.B \-q
Suppress all messages and statistics printed to standard error.
.TP
.B \-v
Print version information and exit.
.TP
.B \-h , \-help , \-\-help
Print usage information and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
0
Successful conversion.
.TP
1
Could not open the PDF file.
.TP
2
Could not open or create the output file.
.TP
3
Copying text from this document is not permitted (encrypted PDF).
.TP
99
Usage error (bad options or missing arguments).
.SH EXAMPLES
Convert all pages to \fIdocument.txt\fR, removing invalid characters:
.PP
.nf
    pdftofilteredtext document.pdf
.fi
.PP
Convert pages 3\(en7, sending filtered text to standard output:
.PP
.nf
    pdftofilteredtext \-f 3 \-l 7 document.pdf \-
.fi
.PP
Preserve the physical page layout:
.PP
.nf
    pdftofilteredtext \-layout document.pdf output.txt
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR pdftotext (1),
.BR pdftextanalysis (1),
.BR poppler (8)
.SH AUTHORS
